cktop
=====

A Linux terminal system monitor. Reads directly from /proc.

Installation
------------

  go install github.com/ckinan/cktop/cmd/cktop@latest

Upgrade
-------

  GOPROXY=direct go install github.com/ckinan/cktop/cmd/cktop@latest


ckstat
======

A one-shot CLI tool that prints current memory usage.

Installation
------------

  go install github.com/ckinan/cktop/cmd/ckstat@latest

Usage
-----

  ckstat          # human-readable text
  ckstat -o json  # JSON output


ckagent
=======

A metrics agent that exposes system metrics in Prometheus exposition format.
Designed to be scraped by VictoriaMetrics (or Prometheus).

Installation
------------

  go install github.com/ckinan/cktop/cmd/ckagent@latest

Run
---

  ckagent -addr :9110

Metrics are available at http://localhost:9110/metrics.

VictoriaMetrics scrape config
-----------------------------

Create /etc/victoriametrics/scrape_config.yaml (or any path readable by the victoriametrics service user):

  scrape_configs:
    - job_name: ckagent
      static_configs:
        - targets: ['<host1>:9110']
          labels:
            host: '<hostname1>'
        - targets: ['<host2>:9110']
          labels:
            host: '<hostname2>'

Example /etc/systemd/system/victoriametrics.service:

  [Unit]
  Description=VictoriaMetrics service
  After=network.target
  
  [Service]
  Type=simple
  User=debian
  Group=debian
  ExecStart=/home/debian/dev/victoriametrics/code/bin/victoria-metrics-linux-amd64 \
    -storageDataPath=/home/debian/dev/victoriametrics/data \
    -retentionPeriod=7d \
    -selfScrapeInterval=10s
  SyslogIdentifier=victoriametrics
  Restart=always
  
  PrivateTmp=yes
  # ProtectHome=yes
  NoNewPrivileges=yes
  
  ProtectSystem=full
  
  [Install]
  WantedBy=multi-user.target

Example /etc/systemd/system/victoriametrics-vmagent.service:

  [Unit]
  Description=vmagent metrics scraper
  After=network.target
  
  [Service]
  Type=simple
  User=debian
  Group=debian
  ExecStart=/home/debian/dev/victoriametrics/code/bin/vmagent-linux-amd64 \
    -promscrape.config=/home/debian/dev/victoriametrics/config/scrape_config.yaml \
    -remoteWrite.url=http://localhost:8428/api/v1/write \
    -remoteWrite.tmpDataPath=/home/debian/dev/victoriametrics/data/vmagent
  Restart=always

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target

Reload and restart and monitor VictoriaMetrics:

  sudo systemctl daemon-reload
  sudo systemctl restart victoriametrics
  sudo systemctl restart victoriametrics-vmagent
  sudo systemctl status victoriametrics
  journalctl -u victoriametrics -f

See https://docs.victoriametrics.com/victoriametrics/single-server-victoriametrics/ for full VictoriaMetrics configuration reference.

